# Constants and utils colocation

Complements [app-module-structure.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/app-module-structure.mdc) and [28-module-types-colocation.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/28-module-types-colocation.mdc): **`types.ts`** = types; module **`const`** + top-level **`function`** helpers for main class → **`constants.ts`** and **`utils.ts`** in same module folder.

## Rule

In module folder under `backend/` (e.g. `backend/apps/notification-service/src/app/email-yandex-postbox/`):

- **`constants.ts`** — URLs, numeric limits, string prefixes, regexes, frozen literals. No env/schema parsing; keep existing `*-env.ts` (or similar) in folder.
- **`utils.ts`** — Pure helpers (masking, truncation, formatting). Named exports; import from `./constants` when helper needs literal there.
- **Main class file** — `export class …` (service, sender, adapter), Nest decorators, orchestration; **import** from `./types`, `./constants`, `./utils`.

Prefer `constants.ts` / `utils.ts` at module root (same as `types.ts`), not `foo.constants.ts`, unless folder has established exception.

## Exceptions

- **`*.spec.ts` / `*.test.ts`:** local helpers/fixtures OK in test file.
- **Barrels:** re-export from `index.ts` only when folder already uses barrel pattern.

## Bad / good

```typescript
// BAD — const + helpers next to class
const MAX_LOG_BODY_LENGTH = 500;
function maskRecipient(recipient: string) { /* ... */ }
export class EmailYandexPostboxChannelSender { }

// GOOD — constants.ts
export const MAX_LOG_BODY_LENGTH = 500;

// GOOD — utils.ts
import { MAX_LOG_BODY_LENGTH } from './constants';
export function maskRecipient(recipient: string) { /* ... */ }

// GOOD — email-yandex-postbox-channel-sender.ts
import { maskRecipient, truncateForLog } from './utils';
export class EmailYandexPostboxChannelSender { }
```
